From Sherri Nichols Subject Re Why Spanky In article Jon Boone writes Spanky is too slow If he were quicker he would still be But with Slaught and Tom Prince they didn't want to lose Prince in order to bring up that Slaught is about as good as Spanky and Prince is coming along nicely Tom Prince is a year old no hit Think of him as a young Dann I can't begin to fathom why the Pirates have been so afraid of losing this guy who's been in AAA most of the last The Pirates released Kirk Gibson last year because Prince was out of options then eventually sent Prince down anyway and he cleared waivers without a He's another year older and still can't hit why do they think he wouldn't clear waivers now Why would they care Sherri Nichols